@startuml
title Math Value Types - Detailed Class View

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

namespace spk {
	class Vector2<T> {
		+ x : T
		+ y : T
		+ norm()
		+ normalize()
	}

	class Vector3<T> {
		+ x : T
		+ y : T
		+ z : T
	}

	class Vector4<T> {
		+ x : T
		+ y : T
		+ z : T
		+ w : T
	}

	class Rect2D {
		+ position : Vector2
		+ size : Vector2
		+ contains(point)
		+ intersection(rect)
	}

	class Matrix {
		+ identity()
		+ translation()
		+ scale()
	}

	class Quaternion {
		+ identity()
		+ normalize()
	}

	class ApproxValue<T> {
		+ value
		+ epsilon
	}

	class Constants
	class Math
}

spk.Rect2D *-- spk.Vector2
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector2
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector3
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector4
spk.Quaternion ..> spk.Vector3
spk.Math ..> spk.Constants
spk.ApproxValue ..> spk.Math

note bottom
The math layer is intentionally value-oriented: objects are
copied, compared, and passed into rendering or widget APIs.
end note

@enduml
